		<td><b>Mega Man 9 soundtrack rumor = rip off of MM2? ...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ok, I want to put this to rest once and for all. I've heard some people say that Mega Man 9's soundtrack literally rips off Mega Man 2, but I haven't yet detected an exact rip off or even a remote similarity between the two soundtracks. Sure it is a similar style, but I hear no melodies or anything directly taken from 2 and used in 9. Anyone else heard that? I believe it actually says this on the Mega Man 9 page at the Mega Man Home Page.
<br />
<br />"Music: 2 [2] [2] [2] [2] [2] [2]
<br />    Many of the songs are from previous games—mostly Mega Man 2 (though ironically they seem to have chosen all of the really short and repetitive ones from that game). Some of the songs are rather high-pitched and repetitive (Tornado Man’s comes to mind) but the rest of the music isn’t that bad. The opening/ending is pretty nice, for example. A shame it all had to be in mono though. "
<br />
<br />What? Tornado Man is one of the coolest tracks in the game!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


